concepts.label: Engineer
concepts.description: A professional who applies technical knowledge and skills in engineering practice

concepts.label: Public
concepts.description: The general population whose safety, health, and welfare engineers must prioritize

concepts.label: Safety
concepts.description: The condition of being protected from danger, risk, or injury

concepts.label: Health
concepts.description: The state of physical, mental, and social well-being

concepts.label: Welfare
concepts.description: The general well-being and prosperity of individuals or groups

concepts.label: Honesty
concepts.description: The quality of being truthful and straightforward in professional communications

concepts.label: Integrity
concepts.description: Adherence to moral and ethical principles in professional conduct

concepts.label: Objectivity
concepts.description: Making judgments based on observable phenomena rather than personal feelings or biases

concepts.label: Confidentiality
concepts.description: The ethical principle of keeping sensitive information private and secure

concepts.label: Competence
concepts.description: Having the necessary ability, knowledge, or skill to perform engineering tasks properly

concepts.label: Conflict of Interest
concepts.description: A situation where professional judgment may be compromised by personal interests

concepts.label: Prioritize Public Safety
concepts.description: The obligation to place the safety of the public above all other considerations

concepts.label: Truthful Reporting
concepts.description: The obligation to provide accurate and honest information in professional communications

concepts.label: Maintain Confidentiality
concepts.description: The obligation to protect sensitive information from unauthorized disclosure

concepts.label: Practice Within Competence
concepts.description: The obligation to only perform work in areas where one has sufficient expertise

concepts.label: Disclose Conflicts
concepts.description: The obligation to reveal any potential conflicts of interest to relevant parties

concepts.label: Professional Report
concepts.description: A formal document prepared by an engineer containing technical information or recommendations

concepts.label: Professional Statement
concepts.description: A formal declaration or assertion made by an engineer in a professional capacity

concepts.label: Professional Testimony
concepts.description: Expert evidence given by an engineer in a formal proceeding

concepts.label: Consent
concepts.description: Permission granted by relevant parties to share otherwise confidential information
